name: Aurora borealis wrap bracelet
description: This cuff is dazzling with aurora borealis crystal beads and gold memory wire. Aurora borealis beads were created in the 1950s in response to innovations in technology by the Swarovski company. Ultra-thin layers finishes applied to crystals made them shine with more light and fire. Shimmering in a rainbow of colors, these vintage beads are a rare find! Beautiful with a LBD or part of your everyday arm candy.

name: Gold nameplate bracelet
description: Antique nameplate bracelet engraved with "Mary." The marking on the underside reads "Forstner Superior." Forstner jewelry, an American jeweler, was in business from the 1920s until the 1980s and were known for their gold and silver accessories. The piece has aged beautifully over time. 7 inches long.

name: Vintage rhinestone bow earrings
description: Beautiful rhinestone earrings with a gorgeous bow shape are perfect for dressing up for cocktail hour or playing up a tee and jeans. The earrings are screw backs, and measure 1 1/2 inches long.

name: Labradorite and sterling silver cuff
description: Vintage scrollwork frames a medium-sized labradorite stone, all set in genuine sterling silver. Labradorite is a greenish blue gemstone known for its iridescence and variance of color. As you turn it, different hues of silvery green and blue appear, making this piece extra special. This cuff is adjustable so it fits all wrists! Add a vintage flair to any outfit this summer.
